      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(cli): support --file for image generate command",
        "body": "## Summary\nThe `image generate` CLI command was missing the `--file` option that `image edit` already supported. This PR adds `--file` support to achieve parity, forwarding input files to the image generation runtime.\n\nFixes #91734.\n\n## Changes\n- `src/cli/capability-cli.ts`:\n  - Added `\"--file\"` to `image.generate` capability metadata flags\n  - Added `.option(\"--file <path>\", \"Input file\", collectOption, [])` to the `image generate` command registration\n  - Wired `opts.file` through to `runImageGenerate({ file: files })`\n\n- `src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts`:\n  - Added regression test: `forwards input files for image generate`\n  - Added regression test: `reports the expanded image.generate flags in capability inspect`\n\n- `docs/cli/infer.md`:\n  - Common tasks table now notes `--file` for `image generate`\n  - Added `image generate --file` example in the code block\n  - Notes section clarifies `image generate --file` vs `image edit` usage\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm test src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts --run` — 97 passed\n- `npx oxlint --import-plugin --config .oxlintrc.json src/cli/capability-cli.ts src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts` — clean\n- `pnpm build` — clean\n- `pnpm format:fix` — clean\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: `openclaw infer image generate --file <path>` now accepts and forwards input files to the generation runtime, matching the existing `image edit --file` behavior.\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux, Node.js 22, local source checkout, real test image file.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  1. Verify `image generate --help` lists the new `--file` option:\n     ```bash\n     OPENCLAW_PROFILE=dev node scripts/run-node.mjs infer image generate --help\n     ```\n  2. Run `image generate` with an actual file path and prompt:\n     ```bash\n     OPENCLAW_PROFILE=dev node scripts/run-node.mjs infer image generate --file /home/0668000666/0668000666/AI/OpenClaw/test.jpeg --prompt \"a blue sky\" --json\n     ```\n  3. Inspect the published capability flags:\n     ```bash\n     OPENCLAW_PROFILE=dev node scripts/run-node.mjs capability inspect --name image.generate --json\n     ```\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n  Screenshot showing `image generate --help` with the `--file` option:\n  ![image generate --help showing --file option](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/11ea03f0-611e-48be-9fb5-33fbb9f59a04)\n\n  Screenshot showing `image generate --file` executed against a real local file:\n  ![image generate --file execution](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/77b23b09-a281-4e66-b890-f4af18b39a5a)\n\n  Screenshot showing `capability inspect --name image.generate` reporting the new `--file` flag:\n  ![capability inspect showing --file flag](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/96f0acaf-5d79-4522-93d9-6f7b48cef55e)\n- **Observed result after fix**:\n  - `image generate --file <path>` is accepted by the CLI parser.\n  - The file path is forwarded to the image generation runtime; the command reaches the provider dispatch layer and returns a normal \"No image-generation model configured\" runtime error, **not** an `unknown option` parse error.\n  - `capability inspect --name image.generate` reports `--file` in the capability flags.\n- **What was not tested**: Live provider image generation with actual API keys and model configuration; only CLI parsing, capability metadata, and runtime forwarding are verified.\n",
        "branch": "fix/91734-cli-image-generate-file",
